Create daily habit (play every day)
Drive subscription conversions (game as premium feature)
Increase booking frequency (use credits before expiry)
Reduce perceived session cost (₹999 → ₹549 average)
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA
Functional Requirements
✅ AC1: Subscription Gate
-
-
-
-
GIVEN a user is NOT subscribed
WHEN they attempt to access the cricket game
THEN they see "Subscribe to Play" screen with upgrade prompt
AND game is locked/disabled
✅ AC2: Daily Play Limit
-
-
-
-
GIVEN a subscribed user
AND they have already played today
WHEN they attempt to play again
THEN they see "Already played today. Come back tomorrow!" message
-
AND cannot play until midnight IST
✅ AC3: Time Window Enforcement
-
-
-
-
GIVEN current time is after 6:00 PM IST
WHEN user attempts to play
THEN they see "Game closed for today. Play tomorrow before 6 PM!"
AND game is disabled
✅ AC4: Probability Distribution
-
-
-
-
-
GIVEN 1,000 plays
WHEN results are aggregated
THEN FOUR appears 75-85 times (7.5-8.5%)
AND SIXER appears 35-45 times (3.5-4.5%)
AND OUT appears 875-890 times (87.5-89%)
✅ AC5: Wallet Credit Award
-
-
-
-
-
GIVEN user wins FOUR
WHEN game result is processed
THEN ₹50 is added to their wallet INSTANTLY
AND transaction is logged
AND credit expires in exactly 30 days
✅ AC6: Credit Expiry
-
-
-
-
-
GIVEN a wallet credit is 30 days old
WHEN expiry cron job runs
THEN credit is marked as expired
AND removed from available balance
AND user is notified (if >₹50 expiring)
✅ AC7: Checkout Integration
-
-
-
-
-
GIVEN user has ₹100 in wallet
WHEN they book a ₹999 session
THEN wallet credits auto-apply
AND final amount is ₹899
AND wallet balance reduces to ₹0
✅ AC8: Transaction Tracking
-
-
-
-
-
GIVEN any wallet activity
WHEN credit is earned, used, or expired
THEN transaction is logged with timestamp
AND user can view complete history
AND balance is updated atomically
